            Our objective is to launch formal private placement offerings in approximately 24 months. This may take the form of a pooled fund or deal-specific Special Purpose Vehicles (SPVs) under Regulation D, Rule 506(c).
        </p>
        <p class="font-sans text-base text-[#1a1a1a] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Currently, our Partner Vetting pipeline serves exclusively to build a qualified interest base for this future launch. Filling out the Partner Vetting form does not constitute a commitment of capital, nor is it an offer to sell securities. No money is being solicited, and if sent in response, will not be accepted. No offer to buy securities can be accepted and no part of the purchase price can be received until a PPM is delivered to a prospective investor and only through formal subscription documents.
        </p>

